cafes.name: Catopia Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 8001 Wyoming Blvd NE suite c-5, Albuquerque, NM 87113, USA

text.text: Great place to go to hang out and play with some nice and fun cats.  If you’re looking to adopt, this is a great place to do it because you can really spend time interacting with and getting to know the cats before picking one.  The staff were very warm friendly.
A place to bond with cats and adopt if you choose.Would of never knew a pace like this existed. Great staff clean place all around a great experience

It costs 12 dollars for an hour to be in this place. I called ahead and was not told this .48 dollars for 4 people to visit cats for an hour is higher than going to a movie . We planned to spend money on whatever they sold, but the cover charge is too much. Staff are super friendly and the people that could afford the cover charge seemed like they were having a great time.

cafes.name: Turquoise Teapot and Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 1221 Flagman Way STE B5, Santa Fe, NM 87505, USA

text.text: Anything to support the kitties looking for homes! I love cat cafes and Santa Fe’s local cat cafe was no exception. What an awesome concept to support and hopefully find homes for these cats! The outside “catio” was a very unique addition to the cat cafe experience. Coffee drinks were yummy too! Thanks for the experience.

Cute little cafe with new monthly drinks for the season. Cost a little to sit with cats and play with them, money is used for cat care. All cats were friendly and excited. No aggressive cats at all. One little girl cat tried to sit in my purse, would have taken her home in a heartbeat.

Not much to say aside from if you like delicious drinks and spending time with kitties, you will not regret coming here. The human staff were so friendly and welcoming, and the kitty staff were as cute as can be. I love this cat cafe so much❤️
